    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Botanic Garden | Cambridge, Mass.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb. 2. 1872</date>
                    <salute>My Dear Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Your note of the 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> ult. just in.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I have read it to two good observers,—who say the “vermiform piles” are common enough here,—and I should think, if not as common as with you thro’ the season, it was owing to interruption in the dry part of our hot summer.</p>
<p>I know nobody now at hand here who could give a comparison with your country. Perhaps I may find some one in Canada to ask.</p>
<p>Now, pray don’t run off on some other track till you have worked out and published about Drosera &amp; Dionæa<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>My wife<ref target="#foot.f3"/> joins in kindest regards to you and yours | Ever Yours sincerely | Asa Gray</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="annotations">
                <note>4.1 Now, … Dionæa 4.2] <hi rend="italic">crossed pencil</hi></note>
                <note><hi rend="italic">Top of letter</hi>: ‘Keep’ <hi rend="italic">red crayon</hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8158.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Asa Gray, 15 January 1872</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had worked on <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Dionaea</hi> intermittently since 1860 (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vols. 8–15, 17–19). The results of this research appeared in 1875 in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4097.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi></ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1960.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Jane Loring Gray</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
